288
00:21:17,880 --> 00:21:19,559
You're pretty good at chess.

289
00:21:19,599 --> 00:21:21,599
- Come and play with me if you're free, alright?
- Yes.

290
00:21:21,960 --> 00:21:23,359
Right. Let's clear the board

291
00:21:23,400 --> 00:21:24,599
and have dinner.

292
00:21:26,680 --> 00:21:27,480
Oh?

293
00:21:31,759 --> 00:21:32,880
Hello.

294
00:21:33,440 --> 00:21:34,240
Right.

295
00:21:35,559 --> 00:21:36,430
Oh, sweethearts!

296
00:21:36,640 --> 00:21:37,720
Come here, guys.

297
00:21:38,480 --> 00:21:40,240
Rak, come here! Quickly!

298
00:21:40,519 --> 00:21:41,920
Lucky me, the traffic was good.

299
00:21:42,799 --> 00:21:44,200
How about that? No need for a surprise.

300
00:21:44,319 --> 00:21:45,519
It's from your favorite place.

301
00:21:45,799 --> 00:21:47,559
I stood in the long line for this.

302
00:21:47,599 --> 00:21:48,559
Here, help each other out.

303
00:21:48,599 --> 00:21:49,920
- Let me put this away.
- How is it?

304
00:21:49,960 --> 00:21:50,960
Do you like it? Take a look.

305
00:21:51,119 --> 00:21:53,150
- I'll save it for later if you don't mind.
- Sure thing.

306
00:21:53,190 --> 00:21:54,519
Put it in the fridge, okay?

307
00:21:54,720 --> 00:21:55,400
Right...

308
00:21:56,190 --> 00:21:57,990
- Hi, dear.
- You're just in time for dinner.

309
00:21:58,279 --> 00:21:59,299
I'm starving!

310
00:22:00,119 --> 00:22:00,960
Thank you.

311
00:22:01,000 --> 00:22:02,400
Whoa, we're having this much food?

312
00:22:02,640 --> 00:22:03,640
Isn't this too much?

313
00:22:04,960 --> 00:22:05,680
No, it isn't.

314
00:22:05,720 --> 00:22:07,700
- Hello!
- We've got many people here today.

315
00:22:08,240 --> 00:22:09,559
Whoa!

316
00:22:11,400 --> 00:22:12,720
Make sure you enjoy all of the food, Father.

317
00:22:12,759 --> 00:22:14,079
- Whoa!
- Here.

318
00:22:14,119 --> 00:22:15,359
How much rice would you like, Father?

319
00:22:15,880 --> 00:22:17,200
- A scoop is enough.
- Here.

320
00:22:17,240 --> 00:22:18,039
That's enough.

321
00:22:18,279 --> 00:22:19,079
And you?

322
00:22:19,240 --> 00:22:20,160
Here.

323
00:22:20,200 --> 00:22:21,720
- Not too much.
- Right.

324
00:22:23,000 --> 00:22:24,000
Get the timer going.

325
00:22:24,640 --> 00:22:25,319
I'm hungry.

326
00:22:25,359 --> 00:22:27,160
Where are you, Rak?
Why are you taking so long?

327
00:22:27,480 --> 00:22:29,359
- Would you like to try this?
- Dad, the timer starts now.

328
00:22:29,400 --> 00:22:30,410
Quickly, Rak!

329
00:22:30,599 --> 00:22:31,599
Rak, everyone's hungry!

330
00:22:37,359 --> 00:22:38,240
Is that enough?

331
00:22:40,599 --> 00:22:41,599
Yes.

332
00:22:43,200 --> 00:22:44,400
Thanks, Fah.

333
00:22:45,759 --> 00:22:47,359
Do you want some cakes?

334
00:22:47,559 --> 00:22:48,359
Oh, sure.

335
00:22:48,480 --> 00:22:50,079
Mom prepared them with love, too.

336
00:22:51,839 --> 00:22:53,000
- They're called fish cakes, dear.
- Oh!

337
00:22:53,039 --> 00:22:54,039
Sorry.

338
00:23:10,039 --> 00:23:11,440
When should we reveal it to your dad?

339
00:23:16,759 --> 00:23:19,519
I think we'll do it after blowing out the candles.

340
00:23:20,680 --> 00:23:21,400
Mm.

341
00:23:26,240 --> 00:23:27,539
By the way, Muenfah.

342
00:23:28,119 --> 00:23:31,359
It's so nice to see that
Babe invited you to the birthday party.

343
00:23:31,640 --> 00:23:33,039
It's been so long, hasn't it?

344
00:23:33,519 --> 00:23:35,000
Your friends aren't coming here, too?

345
00:23:36,400 --> 00:23:37,480
Oh, well...

346
00:23:37,799 --> 00:23:40,240
They're all busy, so he's here all by himself.

347
00:23:40,990 --> 00:23:41,990
Right.

348
00:23:47,519 --> 00:23:48,400
Right...

349
00:23:49,599 --> 00:23:50,599
Dad.

350
00:23:56,079 --> 00:23:58,039
I was the one who invited him here.

351
00:23:59,279 --> 00:24:00,000
What?

352
00:24:00,240 --> 00:24:01,400
So it wasn't Babe...

353
00:24:02,599 --> 00:24:05,200
You're also close to Muenfah as well?

354
00:24:08,599 --> 00:24:09,400
Yes.

355
00:24:12,079 --> 00:24:13,079
So it wasn't Babe?

356
00:24:14,440 --> 00:24:15,440
No, I mean...

357
00:24:16,039 --> 00:24:18,119
I thought you were close friends with...

358
00:24:18,160 --> 00:24:19,759
Shall we bring out the birthday cake?

359
00:24:20,160 --> 00:24:21,599
- He's done with savory dishes.
- I'm full.

360
00:24:21,640 --> 00:24:22,680
I'm craving desserts already.

361
00:24:22,720 --> 00:24:23,930
Let me bring it here real quick.

362
00:24:23,970 --> 00:24:24,970
- Okay.
- Right, please get the cake.

363
00:24:25,319 --> 00:24:26,119
I'll leave that to you.

364
00:24:26,160 --> 00:24:27,160
I'll come with you.

365
00:24:27,480 --> 00:24:29,680
Uh... Are you full, Dad?

366
00:24:29,920 --> 00:24:32,400
Oh, I am.

367
00:24:32,440 --> 00:24:33,640
Okay, okay.

368
00:24:42,839 --> 00:24:46,839
♫Happy birthday to you♫

369
00:24:47,160 --> 00:24:51,160
♫Happy birthday to you♫

370
00:24:51,640 --> 00:24:56,490
♫Happy birthday, happy birthday♫

371
00:24:56,839 --> 00:25:01,839
♫Happy birthday to you♫

372
00:25:02,359 --> 00:25:03,880
Happy birthday, Grandpa.

373
00:25:03,920 --> 00:25:04,720
Here I go.

374
00:25:05,839 --> 00:25:07,440
- Yay!
- Yay!!

375
00:25:10,880 --> 00:25:13,079
This one is from Dom and me.

376
00:25:13,200 --> 00:25:16,319
May you have good health
and stay with us for years to come.

377
00:25:16,359 --> 00:25:17,640
Stay healthy, Grandpa.

378
00:25:17,680 --> 00:25:19,279
- Thank you very much.
- I'll take you out for a soccer game.

379
00:25:19,319 --> 00:25:20,319
Whoa, okay!

380
00:25:21,680 --> 00:25:22,799
- Happy birthday to you.
- Oh?

381
00:25:22,839 --> 00:25:23,880
- Happy birthday!
- You've got yours, too?

382
00:25:23,920 --> 00:25:24,799
That's right.

383
00:25:25,440 --> 00:25:26,960
May you have good health, Father.

384
00:25:27,000 --> 00:25:27,920
This one's from me.

385
00:25:27,960 --> 00:25:28,680
You're going to love it.

386
00:25:28,720 --> 00:25:31,039
The one that you have isn't working well.

387
00:25:31,079 --> 00:25:33,440
- Yours got a dying battery. This is the newer model.
- Oh, right.

388
00:25:33,480 --> 00:25:35,079
Stop overstating!

389
00:25:36,960 --> 00:25:39,000
As for the present from Fah and me,

390
00:25:39,039 --> 00:25:41,680
it's actually the chessboard
you just played on.

391
00:25:41,960 --> 00:25:43,400
I love you so much, Grandpa.

392
00:25:43,440 --> 00:25:44,640
Let me give you a hug.

393
00:25:44,839 --> 00:25:46,039
I love you, my little puppy.

394
00:25:48,880 --> 00:25:50,279
Happy birthday, Grandpa.

395
00:25:50,319 --> 00:25:51,920
May you have great health.

396
00:25:52,400 --> 00:25:54,400
You're very good at chess, actually.

397
00:25:54,759 --> 00:25:56,079
Let's play it again sometime.

398
00:25:56,400 --> 00:25:57,200
Absolutely.

399
00:25:59,039 --> 00:25:59,839
Wait...

400
00:26:00,039 --> 00:26:01,839
Just a second, Teerak.

401
00:26:02,240 --> 00:26:04,839
Why is yours a joint gift with him?

402
00:26:08,759 --> 00:26:10,160
Why isn't it with your girlfriend?

403
00:26:10,359 --> 00:26:12,559
When is she coming?
The one you told me about.

404
00:26:23,259 --> 00:26:24,259
Well...

405
00:26:25,559 --> 00:26:27,319
Fah and I...

406
00:26:28,039 --> 00:26:28,839
Wait.

407
00:26:29,240 --> 00:26:31,440
You call him "Fah"?

408
00:26:33,799 --> 00:26:34,599
Yes.

409
00:26:35,519 --> 00:26:36,519
What does that mean?

410
00:26:42,680 --> 00:26:43,880
Teerak and I...

411
00:26:45,480 --> 00:26:47,119
We're in a relationship.

412
00:26:48,839 --> 00:26:49,559
Huh?

413
00:26:52,599 --> 00:26:53,799
You're joking, right?

414
00:26:55,839 --> 00:26:57,039
It's not a joke, Dad.

415
00:26:59,200 --> 00:27:00,079
Currently...

416
00:27:00,920 --> 00:27:03,119
Fah and I, we're lovers.

417
00:27:05,000 --> 00:27:08,160
When I told you I'd bring my partner over...

418
00:27:10,160 --> 00:27:11,799
I was referring to "Muenfah."

419
00:27:19,759 --> 00:27:21,559
Please let Teerak and me

420
00:27:23,000 --> 00:27:24,200
be in this relationship.

421
00:27:25,079 --> 00:27:26,279
In a relationship?

422
00:27:27,559 --> 00:27:28,559
What the heck are you saying?

423
00:27:28,599 --> 00:27:29,920
This is a birthday party,

424
00:27:29,960 --> 00:27:32,160
not a soap opera.

425
00:27:32,319 --> 00:27:33,759
How would two men be in the same relationship?

426
00:27:33,799 --> 00:27:35,150
Are you crazy? Did you hear that?

427
00:27:35,190 --> 00:27:36,109
- Calm down.
- Calm down?

428
00:27:36,150 --> 00:27:37,480
Didn't you hear them? They've gone insane.

429
00:27:37,519 --> 00:27:38,720
- Please, calm down!
- I'm not staying calm!

430
00:27:38,759 --> 00:27:39,799
Didn't you hear them?

431
00:27:39,839 --> 00:27:40,759
Men being together?

432
00:27:40,799 --> 00:27:41,809
Are you crazy?

433
00:27:42,279 --> 00:27:43,200
I'm having none of this.

434
00:27:43,240 --> 00:27:44,519
- Get out of my house.
- Dad...

435
00:27:44,559 --> 00:27:45,279
- Honey...
- Get out!

436
00:27:45,319 --> 00:27:46,000
- Honey...
- No!

437
00:27:46,039 --> 00:27:47,680
- Teerak, why are you like this?
- Honey.

438
00:27:47,720 --> 00:27:49,160
I don't get it. Explain this.

439
00:27:49,200 --> 00:27:49,920
Why...

440
00:27:50,279 --> 00:27:51,359
Dad!

441
00:27:51,720 --> 00:27:52,599
Honey.

442
00:27:58,079 --> 00:27:59,079
It's fine.

443
00:27:59,240 --> 00:28:00,240
Let him go.

444
00:28:05,440 --> 00:28:07,279
I'll talk to him, okay?

445
00:28:07,680 --> 00:28:09,880
Please return for now.

446
00:28:10,319 --> 00:28:11,279
Muenfah.

447
00:28:11,319 --> 00:28:13,640
I think you should leave now.

448
00:28:13,680 --> 00:28:15,720
Let's wait for him to calm down before we talk.

449
00:28:15,759 --> 00:28:16,960
I can try talking to him.

450
00:28:18,079 --> 00:28:18,799
Fah.

451
00:28:18,920 --> 00:28:20,519
Let them deal with their family matters first.

452
00:28:20,680 --> 00:28:21,440
Let's go.

453
00:28:21,880 --> 00:28:23,059
You should leave now.

454
00:28:23,640 --> 00:28:24,690
Let us deal with this ourselves.

455
00:28:25,160 --> 00:28:25,960
Leave now.

456
00:28:26,240 --> 00:28:27,839
Please. Please leave, dear.

457
00:28:35,039 --> 00:28:36,240
Fah, let's go.

458
00:28:56,519 --> 00:28:57,319
Babe,

459
00:28:57,789 --> 00:28:59,400
take him upstairs, okay?

460
00:28:59,880 --> 00:29:00,599
Go.

461
00:29:01,960 --> 00:29:02,720
Hey!

462
00:29:02,759 --> 00:29:03,960
Honey.

463
00:29:04,400 --> 00:29:05,200
- Let go.
- Dad.

464
00:29:05,240 --> 00:29:06,119
Let go of him.

465
00:29:06,160 --> 00:29:07,000
- Rit!
- Hey!

466
00:29:07,359 --> 00:29:08,240
Let him go.

467
00:29:10,000 --> 00:29:10,920
Listen to me.

468
00:29:11,200 --> 00:29:12,519
Don't date a man, okay?

469
00:29:12,759 --> 00:29:14,279
It'll come crashing down anyway.

470
00:29:14,440 --> 00:29:16,359
Even though it's widely accepted,

471
00:29:16,400 --> 00:29:19,279
you must build a perfect and complete family.

472
00:29:19,319 --> 00:29:21,319
How will I sleep soundly if you're like this?

473
00:29:21,880 --> 00:29:23,039
I love Fah.

474
00:29:24,519 --> 00:29:26,039
If I want to have a family in the future,

475
00:29:26,079 --> 00:29:27,680
I want Fah to be a part of it.

476
00:29:27,839 --> 00:29:30,039
You're too young to understand what a family is.

477
00:29:30,200 --> 00:29:31,799
You're still going to meet new people.

478
00:29:31,960 --> 00:29:33,880
Men being together is doomed to fail.

479
00:29:34,000 --> 00:29:34,799
Believe me!

480
00:29:34,839 --> 00:29:36,440
- Break up with him!
- Do I have to?

481
00:29:38,480 --> 00:29:40,039
Why aren't you giving us a chance?

482
00:29:40,400 --> 00:29:42,000
- What's wrong with it?!
- Listen!

483
00:29:44,039 --> 00:29:45,559
I told you to fucking break up with him!

484
00:29:45,599 --> 00:29:47,039
Break up with him!

485
00:29:47,079 --> 00:29:48,480
Don't fucking let me repeat myself again!

486
00:30:05,240 --> 00:30:06,319
Understand?

487
00:30:07,160 --> 00:30:08,359
Do you understand what I said?!

488
00:30:08,400 --> 00:30:09,960
- Dad! Dad!
- Stop! Snap out of it!

489
00:30:10,000 --> 00:30:11,359
Stop it!

490
00:30:11,400 --> 00:30:12,200
Stop!!

491
00:30:30,640 --> 00:30:32,039
Have a rest upstairs.

492
00:31:00,880 --> 00:31:01,759
Babe.

493
00:31:02,359 --> 00:31:03,740
What should I do?

494
00:31:07,079 --> 00:31:08,079
Calm down.

495
00:31:08,240 --> 00:31:09,640
Give him some time.

496
00:31:10,559 --> 00:31:12,160
We can talk to him again later.

497
00:31:15,039 --> 00:31:16,039
I don't get it.

498
00:31:17,160 --> 00:31:19,480
He seemed to understand about this.

499
00:31:19,920 --> 00:31:21,319
He even watched a boys' love series.

500
00:31:22,839 --> 00:31:24,240
But when it comes to me...

501
00:31:32,240 --> 00:31:34,240
I don't want to break up with Fah, Babe.

502
00:31:35,079 --> 00:31:36,960
I don't want to break his heart.

503
00:31:39,920 --> 00:31:41,119
I get it.

504
00:31:43,480 --> 00:31:45,079
Have a rest for now.

505
00:31:45,680 --> 00:31:46,680
Okay?

506
00:32:30,440 --> 00:32:31,880
[Muenfah: I've made it back to my place]

507
00:32:39,680 --> 00:32:42,200
[Teerak: My brother's sleeping]

508
00:32:42,240 --> 00:32:44,440
[Teerak: Don't you worry, okay?]

509
00:32:50,240 --> 00:32:51,440
[Muenfah: Thank you]

510
00:34:17,199 --> 00:34:19,000
Wow, these look really good.

511
00:34:19,599 --> 00:34:22,039
Babe, take your brother home
right after classes, okay?

512
00:34:22,199 --> 00:34:23,400
Don't dawdle.

513
00:34:24,880 --> 00:34:25,679
Okay.

514
00:34:27,840 --> 00:34:29,280
Take the desserts with you.

515
00:34:30,639 --> 00:34:33,199
I'll share these with Teerak
on the way to the college.

516
00:34:33,239 --> 00:34:34,840
Bring all of them.

517
00:34:34,880 --> 00:34:36,079
Give some to your friends as well.

518
00:34:36,400 --> 00:34:37,889
- Thank you.
- You're welcome.

519
00:34:48,800 --> 00:34:51,000
I'll go check on him.

520
00:35:04,400 --> 00:35:06,000
Are you happy

521
00:35:06,800 --> 00:35:08,400
seeing him like this?

522
00:35:10,440 --> 00:35:12,239
If it makes him happy,

523
00:35:13,079 --> 00:35:15,679
we should be, too, shouldn't we?

524
00:35:18,280 --> 00:35:19,159
Yes.

525
00:35:20,119 --> 00:35:21,980
I'm doing all of this

526
00:35:22,019 --> 00:35:23,420
because I care about him.

527
00:35:27,599 --> 00:35:29,599
I know you do,

528
00:35:31,199 --> 00:35:33,000
but the way you're expressing it

529
00:35:33,760 --> 00:35:35,760
might be hurting him.

530
00:35:38,480 --> 00:35:40,920
I want you to think about this again.

531
00:35:42,519 --> 00:35:43,920
Please.

532
00:36:11,159 --> 00:36:13,159
[Punlee: I'm at the college]

533
00:36:18,840 --> 00:36:20,840
[Punlee: Right here]

534
00:36:27,320 --> 00:36:29,320
[Ghlaijai: That's on my way]

535
00:36:30,119 --> 00:36:32,119
[Ghlaijai: I'll come to you]

536
00:36:36,920 --> 00:36:37,719
Rak!

537
00:36:39,280 --> 00:36:40,079
Hey, Rak!

538
00:36:48,519 --> 00:36:49,400
What's wrong?

539
00:36:50,440 --> 00:36:51,639
Why the long face?

540
00:36:53,519 --> 00:36:55,119
My dad doesn't like Fah.

541
00:36:58,440 --> 00:37:00,440
He wants us to break up.

542
00:37:01,880 --> 00:37:02,760
Shit...

543
00:37:03,559 --> 00:37:04,760
Are you serious?

544
00:37:05,840 --> 00:37:07,239
Does Fah know about this yet?

545
00:37:17,400 --> 00:37:18,639
What's wrong, Teerak?

546
00:37:24,820 --> 00:37:27,019
- His dad wants him to break up with Fah.
- What?

547
00:37:34,960 --> 00:37:36,440
Teerak, are you okay?

548
00:37:39,039 --> 00:37:42,840
I believe you and Muenfah
can go through this.

549
00:37:50,280 --> 00:37:52,280
Right now, the greatest support you have

550
00:37:52,599 --> 00:37:54,599
is being there for each other.

551
00:37:58,840 --> 00:37:59,920
Thanks.

552
00:38:09,599 --> 00:38:11,320
You're amazing, Saggy Cheeks.

553
00:38:26,400 --> 00:38:27,400
Answer it.

554
00:38:28,000 --> 00:38:30,599
Talk it out with him
to figure out the solutions.

555
00:38:38,119 --> 00:38:39,320
Yes, Fah.

556
00:38:40,639 --> 00:38:42,039
Are you at the college now?

557
00:38:49,599 --> 00:38:52,170
You weren't mad at my dad, were you?

558
00:38:55,199 --> 00:38:56,199
I wasn't.

559
00:38:56,639 --> 00:38:57,719
I understand him.

560
00:39:04,079 --> 00:39:06,280
He wants us to break up.

561
00:39:22,239 --> 00:39:23,840
And do you want to break up with me?

562
00:39:29,440 --> 00:39:31,239
I don't.

563
00:39:34,800 --> 00:39:36,599
I don't want to hurt you.

564
00:39:42,039 --> 00:39:43,239
I think...

565
00:39:44,559 --> 00:39:46,960
I'm going to talk about us with my dad again.

566
00:39:48,159 --> 00:39:49,840
It may have been a little too sudden.

567
00:39:49,880 --> 00:39:51,440
That's why he didn't understand me.

568
00:39:53,719 --> 00:39:55,920
If I can explain it to him again,

569
00:39:58,519 --> 00:39:59,920
though it may take some time,

570
00:40:01,599 --> 00:40:03,199
he will understand me.

571
00:40:09,119 --> 00:40:10,920
If you can't do it alone,

572
00:40:11,639 --> 00:40:13,039
let me help you.

573
00:40:16,039 --> 00:40:18,239
I'll hold your hands
and go through this with you.

574
00:40:32,320 --> 00:40:34,320
I'm willing to do everything for you.

575
00:40:38,639 --> 00:40:40,440
I'll do anything to keep us together.

576
00:40:46,719 --> 00:40:48,519
I love you so much, Fah.

577
00:40:49,800 --> 00:40:51,000
I really do.

578
00:41:00,480 --> 00:41:02,280
I love you, too, my love.

579
00:41:24,480 --> 00:41:26,119
- Oh.
- Hello.

580
00:41:26,159 --> 00:41:28,159
- Hi, you're back?
- Hello.

581
00:41:28,320 --> 00:41:29,639
How was your day? Are you tired?

582
00:41:29,679 --> 00:41:31,159
Let's have dinner.

583
00:41:37,920 --> 00:41:39,280
I'm not hungry, though.

584
00:41:39,320 --> 00:41:40,960
I'm going to bed.

585
00:41:41,960 --> 00:41:43,159
Have dinner.

586
00:41:44,119 --> 00:41:45,920
Don't be headstrong and childish.

587
00:41:59,679 --> 00:42:00,480
Come on.

588
00:42:17,079 --> 00:42:19,400
Are you going with Dom this week, Babe?

589
00:42:19,440 --> 00:42:20,320
Yes.

590
00:42:21,559 --> 00:42:22,559
Okay, so...

591
00:42:22,599 --> 00:42:24,800
I'll take Rak to college
and bring him back home.

592
00:42:45,199 --> 00:42:46,079
Dad,

593
00:42:48,760 --> 00:42:50,960
I want to talk to you about Fah.

594
00:42:54,679 --> 00:42:57,280
I told you I didn't want to talk
about this again, didn't I?

595
00:42:58,599 --> 00:42:59,480
Dig in.

596
00:43:02,159 --> 00:43:04,079
Why are you being so hard on your kids?

597
00:43:05,280 --> 00:43:06,480
They're mature now.

598
00:43:07,119 --> 00:43:09,039
Just physically, and I'm not okay about it.

599
00:43:12,880 --> 00:43:14,440
You two understand me, don't you?

600
00:43:19,519 --> 00:43:21,840
I'm doing this because I care about you.

601
00:43:22,760 --> 00:43:23,760
Yes, Dad.

602
00:43:34,920 --> 00:43:37,119
I'm not leaving the town this week.

603
00:43:37,559 --> 00:43:39,360
Stay with me, both of you.

604
00:43:47,039 --> 00:43:48,039
Come on.

605
00:44:13,559 --> 00:44:14,440
Rak!

606
00:44:17,599 --> 00:44:19,320
I'll pick you up right here
after your classes, okay?

607
00:44:20,639 --> 00:44:21,440
Yes.

608
00:44:21,760 --> 00:44:23,039
Study hard, okay?

609
00:44:56,630 --> 00:44:57,630
You want any help?

610
00:44:57,760 --> 00:44:59,159
I do that every day.

611
00:45:04,519 --> 00:45:05,920
Let me help, okay?

612
00:45:07,800 --> 00:45:09,000
If you want to do anything for me,

613
00:45:10,760 --> 00:45:12,760
I just want you to hear me out.

614
00:45:16,119 --> 00:45:17,920
I want you to listen to me

615
00:45:18,400 --> 00:45:20,039
- that Fah and I...
- Rak,

616
00:45:23,280 --> 00:45:24,880
we're not going to talk about this.

617
00:45:41,599 --> 00:45:42,480
Teerak,

618
00:45:44,199 --> 00:45:46,360
come with me to buy a leash for Mookrob.

619
00:45:48,679 --> 00:45:50,880
You should go. I have to stay with Dad.

620
00:45:51,960 --> 00:45:52,800
Come with me.

621
00:45:52,949 --> 00:45:53,750
I can't.

622
00:45:54,719 --> 00:45:55,760
Come on.

623
00:45:55,800 --> 00:45:56,599
No.

624
00:45:56,760 --> 00:45:57,599
Come with me!

625
00:45:58,800 --> 00:45:59,599
Him.

626
00:45:59,800 --> 00:46:00,599
Dad,

627
00:46:01,519 --> 00:46:04,000
can Rak come with me?

628
00:46:09,519 --> 00:46:10,519
Well...

629
00:46:12,199 --> 00:46:14,800
Go with Babe so that she won't be alone.

630
00:46:16,960 --> 00:46:18,480
Am I allowed to leave the house?

631
00:46:18,860 --> 00:46:19,639
Well...

632
00:46:19,679 --> 00:46:21,159
If you want to, yes.

633
00:46:21,519 --> 00:46:22,320
Okay.

634
00:46:24,239 --> 00:46:25,039
Okay!

635
00:46:25,760 --> 00:46:26,960
Let's change our clothes.

636
00:46:27,880 --> 00:46:29,280
Thanks, Dad.

637
00:46:41,000 --> 00:46:42,599
Babe, is Teerak okay?

638
00:46:43,000 --> 00:46:44,199
Not really.

639
00:46:44,239 --> 00:46:45,440
Dad won't let him go anywhere.

640
00:46:48,079 --> 00:46:48,880
Teerak,

641
00:46:49,559 --> 00:46:51,360
do you want to go somewhere?
I can take you there.

642
00:46:54,960 --> 00:46:56,760
It's okay. I don't think Dad will be mad.

643
00:46:58,400 --> 00:47:01,880
I want to go to an art gallery.

644
00:47:02,199 --> 00:47:03,599
An art gallery?

645
00:47:03,880 --> 00:47:04,679
Okay.

646
00:47:04,719 --> 00:47:06,159
Let's go there.

647
00:47:06,199 --> 00:47:07,639
Come on, we'll take you there.

648
00:47:10,239 --> 00:47:11,440
What kind of art do you want?

649
00:47:11,679 --> 00:47:12,880
I want something...

650
00:47:16,440 --> 00:47:18,440
[Babe: We're here; come in]

651
00:47:21,360 --> 00:47:23,360
Right here.

652
00:47:26,679 --> 00:47:27,880
Wow, there are so many paintings.

653
00:47:40,960 --> 00:47:42,960
Are you guys not coming with me?

654
00:47:44,940 --> 00:47:46,139
I want some meatballs.

655
00:47:46,440 --> 00:47:47,840
You go first. We'll be right back.

656
00:47:47,880 --> 00:47:48,880
We're coming later.

657
00:47:49,679 --> 00:47:50,480
Yeah.

658
00:47:51,960 --> 00:47:52,840
Okay.

659
00:48:03,159 --> 00:48:05,559
I don't like it when he's sad.

660
00:48:05,880 --> 00:48:08,880
Yeah, hopefully, he can smile today.

661
00:48:17,239 --> 00:48:18,159
Thanks.

662
00:48:18,599 --> 00:48:20,400
It's okay. Friends always help each other.

663
00:48:20,639 --> 00:48:22,440
Please help him feel happy again.

664
00:48:24,079 --> 00:48:24,880
You should go in there.

665
00:48:24,920 --> 00:48:26,320
We'll stroll around in the meantime.

666
00:49:15,159 --> 00:49:16,760
"Good Bye My Love."

667
00:49:44,920 --> 00:49:45,920
Fah...

668
00:50:10,559 --> 00:50:12,159
I miss you so much.

669
00:50:41,760 --> 00:50:43,960
So do I; I miss you a lot.

670
00:50:54,239 --> 00:50:55,119
Let's go.

671
00:50:58,360 --> 00:50:59,440
Go where?

672
00:51:00,639 --> 00:51:01,840
Let's go paint something.

673
00:51:10,480 --> 00:51:12,280
You're taking me here to paint?

674
00:51:13,639 --> 00:51:14,440
Yes.

675
00:51:14,780 --> 00:51:16,579
I want you to be free from worry.

676
00:51:18,679 --> 00:51:20,079
Seeing you...

677
00:51:20,280 --> 00:51:22,079
has made me feel a little bit less worried.

678
00:51:25,119 --> 00:51:27,519
But if you get to paint,

679
00:51:27,760 --> 00:51:29,960
I think it'll make you feel better,

680
00:51:30,079 --> 00:51:31,079
right?

681
00:52:48,920 --> 00:52:50,119
You're amazing at this.

682
00:52:50,480 --> 00:52:51,480
Thanks.

683
00:52:52,239 --> 00:52:53,840
Does it look like you?

684
00:52:56,599 --> 00:52:57,400
Mm.

685
00:53:20,039 --> 00:53:21,519
Do you feel better?

686
00:53:22,760 --> 00:53:23,960
I'm a lot better,

687
00:53:24,280 --> 00:53:26,280
but I'm the happiest

688
00:53:26,559 --> 00:53:28,320
cause I get to see you.

689
00:53:30,679 --> 00:53:32,599
I'm happy to see you, too.

690
00:53:33,840 --> 00:53:36,840
I'm glad I asked Babe for help.

691
00:53:41,559 --> 00:53:43,360
You planned this with Babe?

692
00:53:44,559 --> 00:53:45,360
Yes.

693
00:53:46,719 --> 00:53:48,719
I asked her to bring you to me

694
00:53:49,480 --> 00:53:50,679
cause...

695
00:53:51,039 --> 00:53:53,039
I missed you so badly.

696
00:53:58,199 --> 00:53:59,599
I'm sorry.

697
00:54:01,199 --> 00:54:03,599
Dad wouldn't let me explain about us.

698
00:54:19,800 --> 00:54:21,000
Are you tired?

699
00:54:25,360 --> 00:54:26,360
No.

700
00:54:27,280 --> 00:54:29,280
I won't give up on us.

701
00:54:30,719 --> 00:54:32,059
Let me know if you're tired,

702
00:54:32,360 --> 00:54:33,360
okay?

703
00:55:03,840 --> 00:55:04,840
Hi, Dad.

704
00:55:23,280 --> 00:55:24,000
Well...

705
00:55:24,039 --> 00:55:25,050
Hold on.

706
00:55:26,840 --> 00:55:28,039
About Rak...

707
00:55:29,760 --> 00:55:31,239
You understand me, don't you?

708
00:55:32,480 --> 00:55:34,360
I'm doing all of this

709
00:55:36,199 --> 00:55:38,599
because I want him to have a perfect family

710
00:55:38,960 --> 00:55:40,360
and be with someone he loves

711
00:55:40,400 --> 00:55:42,000
who's nice

712
00:55:42,599 --> 00:55:44,000
and can make him feel happy.

713
00:55:50,960 --> 00:55:52,960
Is Muenfah not nice, then?

714
00:55:56,440 --> 00:55:57,320
Well...

715
00:55:57,760 --> 00:55:59,559
It's not like that, but...

716
00:56:00,800 --> 00:56:01,800
I'm scared.

717
00:56:02,320 --> 00:56:03,489
Picturing them...

718
00:56:03,719 --> 00:56:06,960
in the future, I'm scared...

719
00:56:07,000 --> 00:56:09,599
no one would be there to take care of him.

720
00:56:12,880 --> 00:56:14,679
Our son is mature now.

721
00:56:18,320 --> 00:56:20,920
He should be allowed
to decide the direction of his life.

722
00:56:22,559 --> 00:56:24,360
I know you're scared,

723
00:56:25,840 --> 00:56:27,239
but the perfect life

724
00:56:28,239 --> 00:56:30,599
you're talking about

725
00:56:31,760 --> 00:56:33,960
isn't something to push on Teerak right now.

726
00:56:36,760 --> 00:56:38,360
At this moment,

727
00:56:40,760 --> 00:56:42,559
he needs more experience.

728
00:56:43,960 --> 00:56:45,360
Don't you see

729
00:56:47,239 --> 00:56:49,639
how happy he is right now?

730
00:56:52,440 --> 00:56:54,039
Are you not happy

731
00:56:55,039 --> 00:56:56,639
seeing your son like that?

732
00:56:58,480 --> 00:56:59,480
I agree.

733
00:57:01,639 --> 00:57:03,440
It's true that he's still young,

734
00:57:04,480 --> 00:57:06,480
but supporting him from a distance

735
00:57:07,079 --> 00:57:08,639
and being there for him when needed

736
00:57:08,840 --> 00:57:10,320
is a better choice, isn't it?

737
00:57:10,429 --> 00:57:11,630
So you think this is okay?

738
00:57:11,800 --> 00:57:13,119
Why do you think I don't?

739
00:57:15,280 --> 00:57:17,320
Rak's still my grandson

740
00:57:17,360 --> 00:57:19,079
and your son!

741
00:57:19,639 --> 00:57:21,039
He's still the same!

742
00:57:21,280 --> 00:57:22,760
If I were you,

743
00:57:23,760 --> 00:57:25,360
no matter who you want to be,

744
00:57:25,679 --> 00:57:27,280
I would be there for you.

745
00:57:29,639 --> 00:57:31,239
Rak's your son.

746
00:57:31,639 --> 00:57:32,840
You need to know

747
00:57:33,360 --> 00:57:35,079
what you can do for him.

748
00:57:41,679 --> 00:57:43,880
If you're concerned about Muenfah,

749
00:57:45,000 --> 00:57:46,199
and if you're scared

750
00:57:46,639 --> 00:57:48,440
or wondering if he's a bad guy,

751
00:57:49,920 --> 00:57:51,559
only time will tell.

752
00:57:56,800 --> 00:57:58,280
Think about this carefully.

753
00:57:58,559 --> 00:58:02,159
Think about what it is that you truly want.

754
00:58:18,960 --> 00:58:20,760
I know you're disappointed.

755
00:58:23,320 --> 00:58:25,480
So am I.

756
00:58:28,760 --> 00:58:31,000
But he's our son.

757
00:58:32,639 --> 00:58:33,639
About this,

758
00:58:34,880 --> 00:58:36,679
it's not anyone's fault.

759
00:58:38,880 --> 00:58:41,079
It's not your fault to be disappointed,

760
00:58:42,280 --> 00:58:45,280
but he's not wrong
for making his own choices, either.

761
00:58:51,760 --> 00:58:53,159
He's a nice guy.

762
00:58:54,840 --> 00:58:56,440
He's sweet.

763
00:58:58,840 --> 00:59:00,840
You should be proud of that.

764
00:59:05,840 --> 00:59:08,840
Let him make his own decisions, alright?

765
00:59:11,199 --> 00:59:12,199
Please.

766
00:59:12,400 --> 00:59:13,300
Please.

767
00:59:20,599 --> 00:59:21,500
Please.

768
00:59:24,239 --> 00:59:25,239
Okay.

769
00:59:32,119 --> 00:59:33,320
I get it now.

770
00:59:40,960 --> 00:59:42,159
Good, son.

771
01:00:34,440 --> 01:00:36,440
Did Babe tell you

772
01:00:37,559 --> 01:00:39,159
she'd leave with Dom?

773
01:00:40,840 --> 01:00:41,840
Yeah.

774
01:00:45,280 --> 01:00:48,079
So...how were your classes?

775
01:00:49,280 --> 01:00:50,159
They were fine.

776
01:00:55,320 --> 01:00:58,039
Who was that, walking here with you?

777
01:00:58,159 --> 01:00:59,360
I only saw his back.

778
01:01:04,719 --> 01:01:05,920
It was Muenfah.

779
01:01:14,440 --> 01:01:18,519
You've known him for a long time now?

780
01:01:22,480 --> 01:01:25,320
Yes, it's been a long time,

781
01:01:25,519 --> 01:01:27,920
but we got closer when...

782
01:01:28,360 --> 01:01:30,079
he helped me.

783
01:01:31,610 --> 01:01:32,610
Helped you?

784
01:01:34,559 --> 01:01:38,559
You know I didn't know how to say no, right?

785
01:01:39,679 --> 01:01:41,880
I would feel bad to ask for someone's help.

786
01:01:43,840 --> 01:01:47,239
But several times, it brought me...

787
01:01:49,039 --> 01:01:50,239
problems.

788
01:01:59,159 --> 01:02:03,960
However, Fah taught me to be braver

789
01:02:05,119 --> 01:02:06,639
and care more about myself.

790
01:02:08,079 --> 01:02:10,280
My life's happier because of him.

791
01:02:18,960 --> 01:02:20,159
I know.

792
01:02:33,039 --> 01:02:34,119
Listen.

793
01:02:39,440 --> 01:02:40,840
I'm sorry, honey.

794
01:02:46,119 --> 01:02:47,320
I'm sorry

795
01:02:48,679 --> 01:02:52,079
for not listening to you.

796
01:02:54,480 --> 01:02:56,880
I didn't care if you were happy or not.

797
01:03:02,320 --> 01:03:06,039
I want to see you smile again.

798
01:03:12,320 --> 01:03:14,719
I want you to feel happy again.

799
01:03:19,280 --> 01:03:20,159
Alright,

800
01:03:21,960 --> 01:03:23,159
from now on,

801
01:03:24,679 --> 01:03:26,280
if there's anything you want to do,

802
01:03:28,079 --> 01:03:29,280
go for it

803
01:03:30,320 --> 01:03:31,840
and follow your heart.

804
01:03:38,840 --> 01:03:39,840
It's just that...

805
01:03:39,880 --> 01:03:43,079
If Muenfah hurts you one day,

806
01:03:47,119 --> 01:03:48,320
you need to tell me.

807
01:04:06,880 --> 01:04:09,079
Thank you for understanding me

808
01:04:09,360 --> 01:04:11,559
and accepting me for who I am.

809
01:04:24,000 --> 01:04:25,480
Does my hair stink?

810
01:04:27,760 --> 01:04:29,119
You're my son.

811
01:04:29,960 --> 01:04:31,280
It never does.

812
01:05:05,000 --> 01:05:06,480
Dad kissed me on the head.

813
01:05:10,960 --> 01:05:11,960
Give your mom a hug.

814
01:05:12,239 --> 01:05:13,440
I'm so happy.

815
01:05:13,960 --> 01:05:16,360
- I really am.
- Thank you for understanding me.

816
01:05:18,800 --> 01:05:20,199
You're my son;

817
01:05:20,320 --> 01:05:22,119
of course, I understand you.

818
01:05:23,000 --> 01:05:24,639
I'm happy for you.

819
01:05:24,679 --> 01:05:26,079
I really am.

820
01:05:27,440 --> 01:05:28,840
Thank you.

821
01:05:29,039 --> 01:05:30,000
Yeah.

822
01:05:30,159 --> 01:05:32,000
Now that you guys understand each other,

823
01:05:32,039 --> 01:05:34,880
should we invite Muenfah to dinner tomorrow?

824
01:05:34,920 --> 01:05:35,800
Whoa, tomorrow?

825
01:05:35,840 --> 01:05:37,480
I have to work tomorrow.

826
01:05:37,599 --> 01:05:39,280
Come on, you can just go to work

827
01:05:39,400 --> 01:05:41,199
and come back to have dinner together.

828
01:05:42,280 --> 01:05:43,280
Okay!

829
01:05:43,590 --> 01:05:45,989
I'll tell Fah about this.

830
01:05:46,840 --> 01:05:47,719
Sure.

831
01:05:49,880 --> 01:05:51,679
I'm happy for you.

832
01:05:55,670 --> 01:05:57,269
Aww.

833
01:05:59,280 --> 01:06:00,679
You're so sweet.

834
01:06:14,079 --> 01:06:15,079
What?

835
01:06:15,360 --> 01:06:16,159
Hey.

836
01:06:16,920 --> 01:06:18,250
- Dad...
- Babe!

837
01:06:18,289 --> 01:06:19,250
Oh, Babe.

838
01:06:20,559 --> 01:06:21,639
What's wrong?

839
01:06:21,679 --> 01:06:23,880
- Don't cry.
- Are you all good now?

840
01:06:25,199 --> 01:06:27,320
- Come on. Don't cry.
- Yes.

841
01:06:27,360 --> 01:06:28,760
Honey, don't cry.

842
01:06:31,280 --> 01:06:33,679
- Come on. Let's hug.
- Come here.

843
01:06:54,440 --> 01:06:56,519
[Teerak: Are you free tomorrow?]

844
01:06:56,559 --> 01:06:58,960
[Teerak: My mom invited you to dinner]

845
01:07:04,639 --> 01:07:07,440
[Muenfah: I am; are you okay?]

846
01:07:09,320 --> 01:07:10,639
[Teerak: I'm more than okay]

847
01:07:10,679 --> 01:07:12,880
[Teerak: I'll call you tonight]

848
01:07:41,280 --> 01:07:42,159
Grandpa!

849
01:07:42,599 --> 01:07:43,389
Grandpa!

850
01:07:43,719 --> 01:07:44,719
Grandpa.

851
01:07:49,360 --> 01:07:50,360
Hello.

852
01:07:50,840 --> 01:07:52,440
He is unconscious.

853
01:07:53,159 --> 01:07:54,679
Yes, the address is 11/11.

854
01:07:54,719 --> 01:07:55,719
Please hurry up.

855
01:08:15,159 --> 01:08:17,319
Taking our family for granted is frightening

856
01:08:17,680 --> 01:08:19,079
since we often don't realize...

857
01:08:19,680 --> 01:08:21,840
how much we neglect them.

858
01:08:22,000 --> 01:08:23,199
Muenfah,

859
01:08:23,560 --> 01:08:27,560
please make him feel happy.

860
01:08:27,840 --> 01:08:29,039
I promise

861
01:08:29,279 --> 01:08:32,680
to make him the happiest person.

862
01:08:33,000 --> 01:08:34,800
The New Year is just a week away.

863
01:08:34,840 --> 01:08:36,960
Should we get our families together?

864
01:08:37,119 --> 01:08:39,720
I was gonna ask if you have any plans.

865
01:08:39,840 --> 01:08:41,920
I no longer want to go there with you...

866
01:08:42,279 --> 01:08:43,399
as a friend.

867
01:08:43,680 --> 01:08:46,359
Muenfah is lucky to have met Teerak.

868
01:08:46,399 --> 01:08:49,720
They're both lucky to have found each other.

869
01:08:49,840 --> 01:08:50,930
I'm thankful

870
01:08:51,199 --> 01:08:52,640
you came into this world for me to love you.

871
01:08:52,680 --> 01:08:55,279
Thank you, too,
for being with me through all of this.
